"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-why-paris-2024-olympic-athletes-are-sleeping-on-cardboard-beds\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"This story originally appeared inWIREDItalia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This story\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 10}, {\"ngram\": \"inWIREDItalia\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 44}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been translated from Italian.\", \"from\": 46, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 74, \"end\": 81, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9940610766254543, \"rank\": 0.0059190356634696815, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, the athletes' beds at the Paris 2024 Olympics are indeed made of cardboard.\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 164, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes' beds\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 134}, {\"ngram\": \"cardboard\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 163}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The paper-based berth news, which has aroused curiosity and some skepticism aftersome videos of athletescirculated online, was confirmed by the organizers of the FrenchOlympic Games, who let it be known that Airweave, the Japanese company that had managed the athletes' rest in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, has been dubbed the \\\"official bedding supporterof the Paris 2024 Olympic and Paralympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9999941733382587, \"rank\": 4.947063904165532e-06, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 522, \"end\": 532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4279879375243136e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 545, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999966253199, \"rank\": 2.9243653941423065e-09, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The paper-based berth news\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 191}, {\"ngram\": \"curiosity\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 220}, {\"ngram\": \"some skepticism\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 240}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 257}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"the FrenchOlympic Games\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 346}, {\"ngram\": \"Airweave\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' rest\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"official bedding supporterof\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These cardboard beds can be transported unassembled in relatively small containers, and then, once their function is over, they can be recycled.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 709, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These cardboard beds\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"relatively small containers\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"their function\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet despite the paper construction, the beds themselves, once put together properly, have been designed to be surprisingly sturdy-and for good reason.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the paper construction\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"the beds\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"good reason\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We designed these cardboard beds so that they can support up to three or four people jumping, because after winning a medal, people are very happy,\\\" Motokuni Takaoka, founder and president of Airweave, said.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these cardboard beds\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"up to three or four people\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 947}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"Motokuni Takaoka\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"Airweave\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1063}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The introduction of cardboard beds had reignited a controversy that arose during the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The introduction\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"cardboard beds\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"a controversy\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1136}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2020, American cross-country skier Paul Chelimo expressed his concernby posting a video of the bedsand speculating that their apparent fragility could be a way to limit intimacy among athletes.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999982416739, \"rank\": 1.674964742397727e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1213, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Chelimo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Chelimo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Chelimo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Chelimo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his concernby\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"their apparent fragility\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1322}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"intimacy\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The no-sex bed theory, however, was later debunked, with the distancing measures implemented by the Olympic Committee aimed at reducing the risk of Covid infection.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The no-sex bed theory\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"the distancing measures\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"Covid infection\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the ban on intimacy between athletes, which had fueled these concerns at the time, was lifted by the Olympic committee last March.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ban\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"intimacy\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"these concerns\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic committee\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Director of the Paris 2024 Olympic and Paralympic villages Laurent Michaud told Sky News at the time that the committee would begiving out 300,000 condomsto ensure \\\"everybody will have what they are expecting and what they need.\\\"\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4279879375243136e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"score\": 0.9999664055407825, \"rank\": 3.359558764369685e-05, \"text\": \"Sky News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"300,000 condomsto\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"everybody\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As to withstanding the rigors of jumping, celebratory or any other kind, as the athletes' videos show, the beds are designed to withstand the stress of up to 250 kilograms (550 pounds) in weight, as well as have a customizable modularmattresssystem with three blocks in different firmness levels that can be adapted to different athletes' physiques and needs.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rigors\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"jumping\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"celebratory\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1962}, {\"ngram\": \"any other kind\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1980}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' videos\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"the beds\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"the stress\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 250 kilograms\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2080}, {\"ngram\": \"550 pounds\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"weight\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"a customizable modularmattresssystem\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"three blocks\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"different firmness levels\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"different athletes' physiques\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"needs\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The use of the 16,000 cardboard beds withmattressesthat are fully reusable and recyclable for the Paris games is part of a series of initiatives put in place aiming to make these \\\"the Greenest Ever Games,\\\" with another being the cleanup of the Seine River.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3490996595389242e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The use\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"the 16,000 cardboard beds\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2306}, {\"ngram\": \"withmattressesthat\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"initiatives\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"these \\\"the Greenest Ever Games\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"the cleanup\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week,Paris mayor Anne Hidalgodonned a wet suit and goggles, and completely submerged herself in the Seine, where swimming has been banned for the past century, and for 50 years raw sewage was released into the river.\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2538, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3490996595389242e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9998661849954772, \"rank\": 0.00013383287457771026, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a wet suit\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"goggles\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2654}, {\"ngram\": \"the past century\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"50 years\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"raw sewage\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The PR stunt was to prove that the water was now clean enough to stage several Olympic swimming events; and three public bathing areas will open in the Games' aftermath.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The PR stunt\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2762}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"several Olympic swimming events\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"three public bathing areas\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' aftermath\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the cardboard beds, the Airweave mattresses are made in part from recycled fishing lines.\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 3025, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"th